# Spam Filter using Naive Bayes

## Overview

This project is a simple spam filter that uses the Naive Bayes algorithm to classify emails as spam or not spam. It is implemented in Python and utilizes the scikit-learn library for machine learning tasks.

## Features

- Classification of emails as spam or not spam.
- Training the model on custom datasets.
- Predicting whether a new email is spam or not.

## Prerequisites

Before using the spam filter, ensure you have the following prerequisites installed:

- Python (3.6 or higher)
- pandas
- scikit-learn

You can install the required Python packages using pip:

```bash
pip install pandas scikit-learn
